content:
The `FileTree` component renders a hierarchical view of files and folders, commonly used in file explorers or navigation panels.

## Purpose

This component provides a visual representation of a directory structure, allowing users to navigate through folders and select files. It supports expanding and collapsing folders and highlighting the currently active file or folder.

## Key Exports

- `FileTree`: The main component that renders the file tree.

## Props

### `FileTreeProps`

- `nodes` (TreeNode[]): An array of tree nodes, where each node can be either a `FolderNode` or a `FileNode`.
- `activeKey` (string | null): The key of the currently active file.
- `activeFolderPath` (string | null): The path of the currently active folder.
- `onSelect` ((key: string) => void): Callback function invoked when a file is selected. It receives the `key` of the selected file.
- `onFolder` ((path: string) => void): Callback function invoked when a folder is clicked. It receives the `path` of the clicked folder.
- `depth` (number, optional, default: 0): The current depth of the tree level. Used for indentation.
- `pathPrefix` (string, optional, default: ""): A prefix to prepend to folder paths. Used for constructing unique folder paths.

### `FolderRow` Component Props

- `node` (FolderNode): The folder node data.
- `activeKey` (string | null): The key of the currently active file.
- `activeFolderPath` (string | null): The path of the currently active folder.
- `onSelect` ((key: string) => void): Callback function invoked when a file is selected.
- `onFolder` ((path: string) => void): Callback function invoked when a folder is clicked.
- `depth` (number): The current depth of the folder row.
- `pathPrefix` (string): The path prefix for the current folder.

### `FileRow` Component Props

- `node` (FileNode): The file node data.
- `activeKey` (string | null): The key of the currently active file.
- `onSelect` ((key: string) => void): Callback function invoked when a file is selected.
- `depth` (number): The current depth of the file row.

## Usage Example

```tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { FileTree } from './FileTree';
import type { TreeNode } from './lib/tree'; // Assuming TreeNode types are defined in './lib/tree'

const sampleNodes: TreeNode[] = [
  {
    kind: 'folder',
    name: 'src',
    children: [
      {
        kind: 'folder',
        name: 'components',
        children: [
          {
            kind: 'file',
            name: 'Button.tsx',
            key: 'src__components__Button.tsx',
            title: 'Button Component',
          },
          {
            kind: 'file',
            name: 'Input.tsx',
            key: 'src__components__Input.tsx',
            title: 'Input Component',
          },
        ],
      },
      {
        kind: 'file',
        name: 'App.tsx',
        key: 'src__App.tsx',
        title: 'Main Application Component',
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    kind: 'file',
    name: 'index.ts',
    key: 'index.ts',
    title: 'Entry Point',
  },
];

function App() {
  const [activeKey, setActiveKey] = useState<string | null>(null);
  const [activeFolderPath, setActiveFolderPath] = useState<string | null>(null);

  const handleSelectFile = (key: string) => {
    setActiveKey(key);
    setActiveFolderPath(null);
    console.log(`File selected: ${key}`);
  };

  const handleSelectFolder = (path: string) => {
    setActiveFolderPath(path);
    setActiveKey(null);
    console.log(`Folder selected: ${path}`);
  };

  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Documentation Repository</h1>
      <FileTree
        nodes={sampleNodes}
        activeKey={activeKey}
        activeFolderPath={activeFolderPath}
        onSelect={handleSelectFile}
        onFolder={handleSelectFolder}
      />
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

## Icons

- `FolderIcon`: Renders an icon representing a folder. The icon changes slightly based on whether the folder is open or closed.
- `FileIcon`: Renders an icon representing a file.
